========
Repeater
========

A CLI tool that allows your linux machine to broadcast its own WLAN while also connected to another Wi-Fi network giving you the hability to basically use your home computer as an additional access point and essentially creating a Wi-Fi repeater and increase your home Wi-Fi range.

----
NOTE
----
Repeater's functionality is highly dependent on the hardware support and capabilities of the wireless card driver.
For the desired and intended functionality the machine in use wireless card's must support both AP (access point) mode and 
